-# Highlighted article view (Slice D, quick first version): the article's prose
-# with cited claims highlighted; the student clicks one to check it. Interim
-# plain-text rendering — a richer view (via an ArticleViewer refactor) will
-# follow. Bracketed COPY notes are descriptive stubs; the article text/title
-# are data.
.container.narrow.claim-verification-exercise.claim-verification-exercise--article
  .claim-verification-exercise__intro
    %h1= @article.title
    %p
      Click a highlighted factual claim with an inline citation that you want to verify.
      = link_to 'Choose a different article',
          "/courses/#{@course.slug}/verify_claim?choose=1"
  - if @extraction.paragraphs.any?
    .claim-verification-exercise__prose= highlighted_prose(@course, @article, @extraction.paragraphs)
  - else
    %p.claim-verification-exercise__empty
      No cited claims could be extracted. Please try a different article.
